Last Name: 















John C. Carter









John C. Carter is a Civil War enthusiast and independent researcher employed by Christopher Newport University in Newport News, Virginia.















Books by John C. Carter










 










































































Our Staff : Pharmaceutical Process Development : Formulation Optimization : Process Troubleshooting : Carter Pharmaceutical Consulting














































Our Staff 
 


John C. Carter, 
President 

CAREER HISTORY:

Since joining the pharmaceutical industry in 1983, John Carter has held
key positions with increasing responsibilities in the field of drug product
development. He has personally developed many products for Novopharm, as
well as product line extensions for Sandoz and Marion Merrell Dow.  


Mr. Carter has managed teams responsible for the planning and execution
of many product development projects through the stages of: small-scale development
trials, scale-up, registration, and validation. Examples include generic
versions of Zantac™, Aleve™, Altace™, Nuprin™, and
Tagamet™. 
 
As Director of Pharmaceutical Development for Novopharm, Mr. Carter has been
responsible for the direct activities of Pharmaceutical Development Staff
consisting of: Formulation Development, Process Development & Optimization,
Clinical Packaging, and Documentation. Mr. Carter also played a key role
in providing input for the Regulatory Submission Process involving U.S.,
Canadian, and European Regulatory Agencies.  In his role as Manager
of Technical Services for Novopharm, Mr. Carter was responsible for trouble
shooting and resolving formulation and/or manufacturing problems.


Since starting Carter Pharmaceutical Consulting Inc. in 2001, Mr. Carter
has been involved in the development of new drug products, and in the troubleshooting
and resolution of manufacturing problems for many Pharmaceutical companies.
Clients include branded, generic, biotech, and contract focused businesses
in both Canada and the United States.


Mr. Carter's experience in the pharmaceutical industry allows him to provide
his clients with a technically sound yet time-conscious approach to servicing
their technical needs, and he is fully aware of the importance of bringing
each project to a cost efficient completion.

EDUCATION:

Honours Food and Drug Technology Diploma – Durham
College of Applied Arts and Technology, Oshawa, Ontario (1983)


Bachelor of Science  –University of
Waterloo, Waterloo, Ontario (1982)


Achievements:


 1983 Durham College Deans List
 Entered directly into 3rd year
	of Food and Drug Technology program with advanced standing
 1983
	Durham College Silver Medal Award as the highest ranking graduate of any
	3-year Technology program
 1983 Chemistry Institute of Canada Award
1978 Ontario Scholar

 


